<span id="freeTextContainer5867894662387452468">I loved this book. I&apos;ve read it at least twice, and will probably read it again someday. Wolfe takes us into the lives of the Mercury 7 astronauts before they were selected and during their training. It&apos;s been years even since my re-read, but scenes still pop into my mind while I&apos;m writing this. To me, that makes it a really special book.</span>
  <span id="freeText5867894662387452468" style="display:none">I loved this book. I've read it at least twice, and will probably read it again someday. Wolfe takes us into the lives of the Mercury 7 astronauts before they were selected and during their training. It's been years even since my re-read, but scenes still pop into my mind while I'm writing this. To me, that makes it a really special book.</span>
